The Edgeley Public School District is in need of Substitute Teachers and Para Educators for the 2020-2021 school year. To sub for a teacher you must obtain a Substitute License, a teaching degree is not required but certain education requirements must be met. Further information on how to do that can be found by clicking the following link: https://www.nd.gov/espb/licensure/license-information/substitute-license
If you are interested in subbing for a Para educator, no sub license is required; however, you must complete a background check. Please contact the office at 701-493-2292 for more information.

Preparticipation Physical Examinations completed for the 2019-20 school year will be accepted during the 2020-21 school year upon submission of a parent and athlete signed waiver (previously known as Form B). Students who did not have Preparticipation Physical Examinations completed for the 2019-20 school year must complete a Preparticipation Physical Examination for the 2020-21 school year.

What this means is any child that had a physical for the 19-20 season only needs to complete the Part B form for the 20-21 year. All 7th graders will need to have a full physical. We will address any others that have to have a full physical due to potential exceptions.

Please find the Form Part B under the Activity Information tab on our school website. https://ndhsaa.com/uploads/files/NDHSAA-Preparticipation-Form-B.pdf

PLEASE turn these forms into the school office as soon as possible.

post_text: Thank you custodians!
shared_text:
Cassie Dorich‎Edgeley Public School
June 17 at 7:17 PM ·

I thought I would share some behind the scene pictures of what happens in the summer at the school. We have been asked several times by parents. Our custodial/maintenance crew take pride in our work. We strive to have a very clean school that we can be proud of. Summer cleaning involves taking furnature out of the rooms so they can be stripped and waxed or shampooed. We collected almost 60 pounds of wax from just part of a room. We also wipe down classrooms from top to bottom. We have painted walls and replaced white boards. This year we moved everything out the maintenance storage room and Mr Young's room to get ready for the floor project and apply a fresh coat of paint on all the walls. I can say I am very proud of my coworkers and the work they do. RoxAne Swartz, Shannon Augeson, Sandy Anderson, and Dana. We look forward to seeing everyone this next Fall. We have also learned to use the weed eater and the zero turn lawn mowers. That has been quite interesting.

Pre-participation Physical Evaluation (Sports Physical) UPDATE

The Board of Directors approved a NFHS recommendation to allow Pre-Participation Physical Examinations completed for the 2019-20 school year to be accepted during the 2020-21 school year upon submission of a parent and athlete signed waiver (previously known as Form B).
https://ndhsaa.com/uploads/files/NDHSAA-Preparticipation-Form-B.pdf

Please fill out this form if your child completed and submitted a sports physical to their school for the 2019-20 school year. Submit the attached form to the high school office as soon as possible for approval from Mr. Schwartzenberger.

If your child did not complete a physical for the 2019-2020 school year, the following form must be completed and signed by a medical professional prior to their first practice for the 2020-2021 sports season.
https://ndhsaa.com/files/NDHSAA_Physical_Form.pdf

Please contact Mr. Schwartzenberger with further questions.

Statewide Class of 2020

The North Dakota Department of Public Instruction has partnered with the Governor's Office, Forum Communications and Microsoft to produce a virtual Celebration for the North Dakota Class of 2020. This statewide celebration will honor graduates from every high school in North Dakota with a slideshow. Microsoft Teams will enable viewers to listen to guest speakers, including Governor Burgum, Carson Wentz, Josh Duhamel, and a performance by Tigerlily.

The North Dakota Class of 2020 Celebration can be viewed on May 30 at 2 p.m. Central by tuning in to your local ABC station (WDAY, WDAZ, KBMY and KMCY) or by visiting Inforum.com, GrandForksHerald.com, JamestownSun.com, TheDickinsonPress.com or WestFargoPioneer.com. The livestreams will be featured at the top of each news site's homepage and will not require registration or subscription to watch. Please pass this information on to your students and families.

Edgeley High School May students of the month:

Kelly Lund has been a motivated and hardworking young lady during this distance learning experience. She has met deadlines, asked questions when uncertain, and attended class meetings diligently. She always wears a smile and lends a helping hand to anyone who is in need. Over the past year, she has grown tremendously with her independence and academics. Edgeley High School staff members are proud of her growth.

You count! School funding is dependent on Census results, so don't forget to participate! Every 10 years, the United States Government conducts a census and counts all the people who live in the nation. It helps the government determine how education, housing, and social services should be funded in the city you live in. We are all required to complete the 2020 census.

Learn about the importance and what you can do to be counted here: https://www.nd.gov/news-events/census-2020

Edgeley School Resources
March 24 at 1:30 PM ·

Today’s STEM project. Create a boat using only 2 feet of tin foil and 1 foot of plastic wrap and 1 foot of any tape of your choice. You are allowed to use 1 mystery material (can’t be a boat already created). Mystery items could include but not limited to a cork, cardboard, material, straw.... Set your boat sailing in some water. Add pennies and see how many pennies it will hold before sinking. Either snap some pictures or video it. Post your pictures/video on the comments to this post to share with everyone. Good luck! I can’t wait to see your boats!
There will be a new challenges listed here on Tuesdays and Thursdays at 1:30.

March 13, 2020 2:45 pm

FARGO – On Friday, March 13, due to the Emergency Declaration issued by President Trump the NDHSAA will suspend play at the 2020 NDHSAA Class A Basketball State Tournament and all remaining 2020 NDHSAA Winter Postseason State Tournaments including the 2020 NDHSAA Class B Boys Basketball State Tournament.

In addition to the remaining 2020 NDHSAA Winter Postseason Basketball State Tournaments being suspended, all remaining fine arts and spring sports seasons have been suspended indefinitely, which includes practices and game contests. Further information will be released as it becomes available.

Brenda Schell
NDHSAA Assistant Director
